    "narrative": "For LawDog on this April 12th slate, our offensive engine is centered around **Daulton Varsho** (72.31) and **Bryson Stott** (68.66), who command the highest efficiency scores of the day. **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Bradley, carrying a 10% platoon boost and solid park factors, while **Bryson Stott** remains a high-floor asset despite facing a tough arm in Gallen, buoyed by a 13% platoon edge. **Geraldo Perdomo** (68.20) also vaults into the elite tier, capitalizing on a weak 4.82 xERA matchup against Painter. While **Lawrence Butler** and **Jeremiah Jackson** carry solid mid-tier projections, we are keeping a close watch on **Tyler Freeman** (54.70); while he slots into a favorable batting order position, his 39% rain risk creates a volatile ceiling that warrants close monitoring before first pitch.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench today involves **Jung Hoo Lee** (51.29), who narrowly missed the cut behind our starters. While **Jung Hoo Lee** benefits from a park factor surge, the optimizer favored the more consistent platoon advantages offered by **Jonathan Aranda** and the order-derived stability of our core middle infield. Meanwhile, we are exercising extreme caution with our utility slot; **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (54.70) remains in the lineup despite a daunting matchup against Chris Sale. His raw talent maintains his standing, but we are sacrificing nearly 19% in SP skill efficiency to keep him active. Similarly, we have opted to bench **Yainer Diaz** (36.62) today; facing Logan Gilbert\u2019s elite 2.86 xERA makes him an easy fade to preserve our game caps, as his current projected efficiency falls well below our 40-point threshold.",
